definitions.definition: ( mathematics ) A proposition proved or accepted for immediate use in the proof of some other proposition.

subdefinitions.definition: ( in phrases , by extension ) A proposition originally used for such a purpose, but having later acquired a greater, independent, importance; a fundamental (often pithy ) and widely-used result .

definitions.definition: ( linguistics , lexicography ) The canonical form of an inflected word; i.e., the form usually found as the headword in a dictionary , such as the nominative singular of a noun, the bare infinitive of a verb, etc.

( psycholinguistics ) The theoretical abstract conceptual form of a word, representing a specific meaning, before the creation of a specific phonological form as the sounds of a lexeme , which may find representation in a specific written form as a dictionary or lexicographic word.

definitions.definition: The outer shell of a fruit or similar body.
One of the specialized bracts around the floret in grasses .

main_definition: ( botany ) The outer shell of a fruit or similar body.
